<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
Having your car broken into is a pretty horrible experience, but Safelite helps ease the pain and annoyance of getting a new window.

One thing I did not know is the Crash Wrap service Safelite offers. As soon as you have your appointment boooked with Safelite, you can go to their physical location, and they will vacuum the glass from your car and wrap/cover the window with a plastic wrap that sticks to your car without harm to the paint. It somewhat helps keep the outside out, but the noise of having a single window open is still nagging.

A huge benefit of Safelite is that they will come to your location, assuming they have an available appointment in your area. Safelite did not have an available appointment by my place of work at all, so I had to drive home to get it done. This was perfectly fine though, I was able to enjoy my home while the work was done.

The service agent was professional and quick. The window was installed perfectly, as far as I can tell.

The only disappointment I had was that I did not have the option to select after market or OEM parts. I was only notified at the time of installation that it was after market. Therefore, if you want OEM, you will have to call them to place your order instead of ordering onlinle.

Despite the minor annoyances, I give the whole experience the full 5 stars. It is well deserved.< /Review>

Going with Safe Lite would have meant that I would have paid my full deductible, waited over 2 weeks and still in the end have a Chinese aftermarket part, which I'm not comfortable with on my particular vehicle. I didn't like the idea of spending weeks commuting with a crack like that in my view and started digging...

Ultimately, I did not get my repair done here and instead went to Hi-Tech Auto Glass nearby. They were able to install an OEM windshield *the next day* and I only paid my $250 deductible, which was incredible, considering. So, if Safelite makes you wait like they did me -- you're better of looking somewhere else! You won't be sorry. See my review for the other shop for details.< /Text><Response>None<//Response>< Rate>
3<//Rate>

<gmap_id>0x808505fd1f03fa01:0x6036442fb6687e2e<//gmap_id>< text>
This is a beautiful, shady, well-maintained park. I'm only knocking off a star because there are only three trash bins, and they are all at the front third of the park, closer to the entrance. There are also no bathrooms, so be sure to go beforehand. There is a creek bed running the length of the park and it was almost entirely dry (at least when I went, in late May). < review>
I'm not a fan of hawaiian food but I was surprised by how much I enjoyed coming here for lunch. I was tempted to get the chicken and waffles because everyone around me was ordering it but decided on one of their sandwiches. I can't remember which one but it was so good that I'm sure any of the sandwiches there are yummy choices. They also have a good passion tea that paired well with my meal. Next time I will definitely have to try the chicken and waffles!< /review>

< Text>
I had a great overall experience here. The people there are cheerful and seem passionate about the food. To me the food was unique and delicious. I mean come on... Spam and cheese waffles?? Now that's interesting! I ordered the Katsu style chicken Moco with a two stack of apple banana pancakes. The pancakes had a really great thick consistency which was perfectly balanced with the thinner sweet coconut sauce on the side. Fantastic. I'd recommend to a friend without hesitation.< /Text>

<name>Nei Ng</name><Date>1468444798681</Date>< rate>
3<//rate>
<Review>I came here with some old friends, and there was a decent crowd when we arrived. We probably had to wait at least 30-40 minutes to be seated, and then the food took a pretty long time to reach our table. I dunno if it was just an off day or something, but we noticed that people around us also weren't getting their food in a timely fashion. Though whenever we interacted with the staff, they were nice and friendly.

I had the Loco Moco with white rice, and it was just ok. Maybe the line made my expectations too high, but nothing made me say, "So this is what I was waiting for!" Let me start with the good stuff first. The short grain white rice was cooked pretty well and had a nice firm texture. The mushroom gravy also had good flavor. I could definitely taste the earthy depth from the mushrooms, and the grilled onions gave it a crisp sweetness. I thought it could use a bit more seasoning though. Some salt would really make the flavors pop out more.

The worst part of my meal were the ground beef patties. They weren't seasoned very well and were way overcooked. This made them pretty bland, dry, and rough. Mixing it in with the runny egg yolks and gravy didn't really help either. I don't  think the gravy was robust enough to adequately add flavor to the under-seasoned patties.

I would rate the food 3 stars, but the wait time brings it down a little. I'll just say that it's 2.5 stars and rounds up to 3.< /Review><pictures>None<//pictures>< response>
None< /response>

< review>
Really good homestyle Hawaiian food. Their menu seems to lean more towards brunch-y items, so think more dishes with poached eggs on 'em, fewer grilled shortribs. I had the Loco Moco, which was very tasty-- the gravy in particular was delicious, and my wife had the Huveos Rancheros with Kalua Pork which was awesome. (I'm getting that next time.)

Service was friendly, and decor is a touch nicer than your typical Clement Street restaurant. Definitely worth a try next time you're in the neighborhood.< /review>

< Text>
I give and take some with the whole 2020 stuff. Went there to try something different plus had a craving for some sushi. Was cought a little off guard when the entrance was squared off by tables, however, there was someone paying attention to the lobby. The menu was on the left. Chosen the Mango roll and crunchy tuna roll. The Mango roll was the most interesting. Had the sweetness of the mango plus a kick of spice to it, very good. The tuna roll for me was so-so could have been better. Would I go back? Maybe but on a rare occasion. My opinion the prices was a little too pricey but it was interesting doing something different.  Included is the menu I saw and the Mango roll.<//Text>

<Rate>1< /Rate>< Review>
Heard about this place on the news, they gave it some pretty good reviews and I'm always into trying fusion foods... Sadly I was was very disappointed...
First off, the place looks abandoned, very badly maintained, parking lot is small. The interior is nothing special but it was clean...
I ordered 2 rolls. A deep fried roll with fried onions strings (can't recall the name) it was so bland, all I could taste was the breading. The 2nd was a simple shrimp tempura roll, big mistake, shrimp smelled so bad...
My wife was NOT gonna order sushi here, lol...
She ordered the camarones a la diabla. She gave them an ok rating and said the rice and beans were also bland, how can you mess up rice and beans??!! Her saving grace was the hand made tortillas...
I can't recommend trying it this place...</Review>

Although parking may be a challenge, The Mary Pickford proves to be well worth the effort for movie viewing as it should be. Online purchasing secures your seat location before arrival and all you need to do is head over to grab a snack. The theatre outlay provides staggered rows so not to put anybody‚Äôs backside between you and the screen. The seats are a lovely mechanized ‚Äúlazy-boy‚Äù feel that reclines with a hug. Front row thrill seeker or backrow corner relaxer, this place reminds you why people use to go out to the movies. <Review>**This is a review of the building and grounds only.

One thing I must mention is that the museum they had inside is no longer there. Apparently, the family took the items. I went to the theatre to take photos outside and that night read reviews later. The next day I went back, based on those reviews, looking for the Oscar, dress, and other items. That is when I discovered they were not there.  Hopefully this can save someone else the trip if this is what you are looking for.

The outside of the theatre is the old style marque. There is also a marque close to the entrance out by the street. There is construction there by the sign at this time (May 2018). It is located at the Town Square in Cathedral City. Also located there is the Cathedral City City Hall and the Cathedral City Police Department.
There are several bronze statues in the square memorializing notable people. There is also a gorgeous fountain in the center - The Fountain of Life. It is a beautiful display of mosaic art. A must see.
If you are in the area this is a nice place for a walk and also a place to prompt you to read about the remarkable life and accomplishments of Mary Pickford. A woman before her time.</Review><name>Julie</name><gmap_id>0x80db02d9c803d2e5:0xfac252b3f04a40b< /gmap_id>< response>
None< /response>

<userid>112209497970523732050<//userid><name>Jeffrey Dickman< /name><time>1531234299179< /time><rate>4< /rate>< Review>
A nice theater complex located in Cathedral City, adjoining city hall off Highway 111.

I like this venue because it is newer, has covered parking, comfortable seating, and a nice selection of food and a drink, including beer and wine.

Senior prices are pretty good, and matinee prices are decent if you don't mind arriving before the higher priced evening shows.

I'm glad the city has this business in town, otherwise folks would need to enjoy their movie watching elsewhere.</Review>

< review>
The absolute best theater in Palm Desert and surrounding. Each seat has its own wide armrest. Each seat has two of its own soda/candy holders. Each chair learns back like your lazy boy chair at home. Sounds is modern and exceptional. Many theaters/films to pick from. Parking is free. Food served as well as the usual theater food and beer and wine available.  Beautiful setting inside and out with tables inside. Rarely packed, often in theater with one or two with me. Many commercials before the previews but that gives you time to eat, do your social media. Simply the only theater to go to.</review>

< text>
Every screen I have been to at this theater has been of ample size and with great sound (and at the proper volume!). The seats have also been great, and the staff is nice. And unlike EVERY regal and century theater I have been to, they actually mask the grey bars above and below the projected images. They also let you reserve seats in advance with moviepass. Whenever possible, I will choose this theater over the regal and century etc theaters in the area.< /text>

< Text>
I am 5'2" tall. My femurs are about 7 inches too short for me to sit in the chairs here. My husband, just under 6 feet, is not the right size either. I sat on the edge of my seat for 2.5 hours, because if I sat all the way back my legs would have been sticking straight out in front of me. The sound was so loud my ears are still ringing nearly a week later, and my lower back still hurts. It's as if someone thought "bigger is better, and louder is better." Not for us. If you are exceptionally tall, and hard of hearing, this is D Place for you. We will not return.<//Text>

< Review>
This is our Go To theater.  We live close by so haven't had alot of experience at the other theaters in the valley. That being said, we love the reclining chairs!! You can actually curl up, they are that roomy! Concession stand has a very large menu including beer or wine. Everything is expensive but I think that is true in most venues. I'm just glad I dont have children going to the movies! Employees are all helpful and nice. Juan and Miriam are friends we just haven't done lunch with! Very pleasant entry area with Mary Pickford memorabilia. Arcade games that I have zero idea about! All and all a nice, clean, cool to be on some of our hot days! Just give it a peek see.<//Review>

<user_id>113099315709673133097</user_id><user_name>Paisleystorm Page<//user_name><time>1531713815642<//time><rating>5<//rating><review>Wonderful theater!  Outside was beautiful architecture.  It does not look like a modern theater from outside. Inside was a very modern multiscreen theater, excellent concessions, nice food offerings beyond popcorn, soda, espresso bar, pizza, cinabons, serve your self butter and they had alcohol as well.

The seats though, they are the very best movie theater seats ever!!  Even better than the seats at places that are determined "luxury" for thier seats.

These were comfortable, recliners with huge cup holders and individual arm rests (no bumping elbows with scrubs.) The seats were spaced perfectly above and below, wide aisles and well lit on the ground. The seats were not the kind that make you feel tired though, Thankfully.  I hate to pay to take a nap.<//review>< Pics>

< Review>
I have been to the regular theaters here before with the reclining chairs and enjoyed it. The concessions are good, but not too different from most theaters. The most excellent aspects of this theater are it's location, a real highlight of Cathedral City, and the Barco DBox. I have been to a 4D theater before and did not really enjoy it. The DBox is much more subtle and enjoyable. I highly recommend this theater.</Review>
